race.comment: ELIZABASS (5) finished out of the money two starts back then was beaten 10 lengths when tenth over 1200m at Warwick three-and-a-half weeks ago. Has the ability to put the recent run of form behind her. CEEKAY'S CHOICE (4) finds it hard to win with just one success from 12 starts. Again tasted defeat last start when fourth over 1200m at Warwick, beaten 2.75 lengths. Has the talent to take care of this field. BRAVE EMMA (8) accounted for a maiden field over 1000m at this track last start, finishing one length ahead of the nearest rival. This is tougher but she cannot be underestimated. MR WANDJI (2) fought on for third last start over 1200m at Miles, beaten 12 lengths to add to some fine recent form. Nicely placed to give this a mighty shake.
